      },
      "lineNbr": 26,
      "author": {
        "id": 11964
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-11T19:28:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If garbage is passed for input, the worst that can happen is that the dataChunk stays set as 0. Then when we try to read the data, there is a check:\n\nif (mDataChunk \u003d\u003d 0 || mFmtChunk \u003d\u003d 0) {\n        return 0;\n}\n\nWe can handle it on our end to avoid unnecessary work though. I\u0027ll make another CL.",
      "parentUuid": "4560d9e1_b967e711",
      "revId": "726e35fcff23d7b052faf8d9d29120ec532b2aa8",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
